The paper discusses Fano's inequality and its variants in the context of statistical estimation, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also covers a wide range of specific problems, including group testing, graphical model selection, sparse linear regression, density estimation, and convex optimization, which are all areas that could fall under different sub-categories such as data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
